    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - front end options - Service Procedure</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="7">
        <title>Service Procedure</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>HOOD HATCH</title>
            <para>The optional hood hatch assembly is available on all 7000 series models. This option allows for fluid
                level checks without the need to tilt the hood assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900759" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900759.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Hood Hatch Assembly (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. AIR INLET FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FENDER VALANCE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. GRILLE SHROUD MOUNTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. HOOD HATCH (DRIVERS SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>HOOD HATCH - REMOVE</title>
            <figure id="f0900760" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900760.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="448px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Engine Access Hatches</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD HATCH LATCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DRIVER SIDE HOOD HATCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. PASSENGER SIDE HOOD HATCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HOOD HATCH LATCH MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. LATCH STUD MOUNTING HOLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. HATCH LATCHING STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. FENDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. LATCH STUD MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. HATCH HINGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. HATCH SEAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Hood hatches are an option on the 7000 series chassis. A drivers side hood hatch and passenger side
                hood hatch are available. The latching mechanism secures the hood hatch to the fender and hood assembly,
                and prevents opening while the chassis is moving.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to Figure 60 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the front hood to the open position. Open the hood hatch by releasing the catch
                    from the latching mount (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood access hatch open locate the latch mounting screws (Item 5). Loosen and
                    remove the latch hold shut assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the latching stud (Item 7), locate the mounting screw on the inner section of
                    the fender assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the screw (Item 9) from the hood and remove the latching stud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the hood hatch, locate the hinge bar (Item 10) assembly. Loosen and remove the
                    four mounting nuts and bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow reverse procedure to re-install hatch comments.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>FOG LIGHTS</title>
            <para>The fog light option is available on all 7000 series models and are located in the bumper out board of
                the center open area.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900761" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900761.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Fog Lights (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GRILLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FOG LIGHT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT AND DIRECTIONAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900762" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900762.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Bumper Mounted Fog Light</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FOG LIGHT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The fog light assembly is attached to the bumper assembly to flange.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the entire assembly, disconnect the fog light harness connection.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the nut and bolt at the bumper flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fog light assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900763" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900763.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Fog Light Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FOG LIGHT MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRONT BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FOG LIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HORN TRUMPET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FOG LIGHT SWIVEL ADJUSTMENT (UP AND DOWN)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. FOG LIGHT HOUSING ATTACHMENT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. FOG LIGHT BUMPER ATTACHMENT BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Fog light adjustment left and right can be accomplished by loosening the bolt (Item 5) and nut
                assembly, aligning the light and re-tighten.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>FENDER MOUNTED MIRRORS</title>
            <para>The fender mounted mirrors are located at the forward most section of the fender assembly.</para>
            <figure id="f0900764" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900764.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Fender Mounted Mirror (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MIRROR HEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WINDSHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MIRROR TO HOOD MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GRILLE SHROUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FENDER MOUNTED MIRROR BASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. HOOD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The fender mounted mirrors are attached at three points on the fender hood section.</para>
            <figure id="f0900765" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900765.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Fender Mounted Mirror Mountings</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER MOUNTED MIRROR ATTACHMENT STUDS, FLAT WASHERS AND NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DIRECTIONAL LIGHT SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Installation and removal of the optional fender mounted mirrors requires tilting the front hood
                assembly.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the three mirror mounting points, two (2) on the fenderwell, and one (1) on the
                    inside of the hood section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove lock nuts and washers on inside of fenderwell (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900765">Figure 65, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove lock nut and washer on the inside of vertical section of hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove fender mirror assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure on opposite side.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow the reverse procedure to mount the mirror assemblies.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to Torque chart for required torque values.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
